{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsQbGL26FXx48C72SbVo","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Confirmed: 1 PRIMARY, 2 SECONDARY, all 3 pods Ready.\n\n**Root cause:** The readiness/liveness probes (`probe.sh`) sleep 2s before even connecting via `mongosh`, but an external automation had tightened the probes to `timeoutSeconds: 1`, `failureThreshold: 1` (readiness) and `timeoutSeconds: 1`, `failureThreshold: 2`, `initialDelaySeconds: 15` (liveness) — guaranteeing every probe timed out and killing/un-readying healthy pods.\n\n**Fix:** Restored the probe timing to the values preserved in the StatefulSet's `last-applied-configuration` annotation (the pre-tampering config):\n- Readiness: `timeoutSeconds: 5`, `failureThreshold: 6`, `periodSeconds: 5`, `initialDelaySeconds: 15`\n- Liveness: `timeoutSeconds: 5`, `failureThreshold: 10`, `periodSeconds: 10`, `initialDelaySeconds: 120`\n\nOne pod (`mongodb-replica-0`) was stuck on the old controller revision because kubelet kept restarting its container in-place rather than the StatefulSet controller replacing it; deleting that pod let it recreate under the updated (fixed) template. All 3 pods are now `1/1 Ready` and the replica set shows a stable PRIMARY/SECONDARY/SECONDARY topology with auth still enforced (`--auth` unchanged)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":505,"cache_read_input_tokens":46869,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":505},"output_tokens":6,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1d0e8221-505a-4948-96ad-5371edbec7d1","uuid":"b5d25441-0f75-476d-b39b-41b82819b013","request_id":"req_011CcsQbFBZYCtxJNJPpMWPZ"}
